rComments: He made a class that would have otherwise been very boring very fun very interesting. I'll never forget his Scottish accent and humorous class examples. I'm surprised at some of the previous reviews. Now keep in mind he does do pop quizes, but I think they actually help, so you can see if you truly understand the concepts. He genuinely does care.

Awful professor, due to a lack of clarity the course content is often times over complicated in lecture. Tests and assignments are ambiguous and place a large emphasis on SPSS which is only a portion of the course.

Worst. Professor. Ever.  Most disorganized and poorly taught class at U of T.  Tutorials are mandatory yet useless, and even he doesn't know what material is important. Class has to do with statistics yet the assessments are based on pushing the right buttons on a computer program. Assignment was incredibly confusing and he offered no help at all
